# CSVI C Standards

- No `exit()` in library code under `src/lib/` — return error codes or NULL; only `main` and the app layer terminate the process.
- Every `malloc`/`calloc` has a matching `free` on all paths.
- Use `const` for read-only pointer parameters.
- Prefer `size_t` for indices and lengths.
- snake_case for functions, types, and struct fields (no camelCase).
- Headers use include guards (`CSVI_*_H_`).
- Includes: `-I src/lib`, paths like `#include "io/csv-reader.h"`.
- New source files belong under the correct layer: `common/`, `io/`, `layout/`, `ui/`, `nav/`, `cmd/`, `app/`.
- Non-UI logic changes require tests in `tests/`; run `make check`.

```c
// BAD — library calls exit
if (!fp) { fprintf(stderr, "error\n"); exit(1); }

// GOOD — propagate error
if (!fp) {
    snprintf(errbuf, errbuf_len, "could not open '%s'", path);
    return NULL;
}
```
